{
  "stem": "21582.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were-- everything was kind of-- we were-- it was-- we were constantly at the mercy and whim of the Germans.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- please remind me of it if I-- if I omit it, because they did happen after the-- after the ghetto was-- after the wall was built, probably more so they became-- some of the things that happened that will describe that.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I'll get back to that, and please don't let me forget.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then-- then I don't recall what accounted for the closing of that ogrodek.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we had tutors.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was very, very common.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You saw-- often saw parents who were swollen with hunger, and I don't remember if I mentioned the bread was rationed, that they really traded their meager rations so that they can use it in exchange pay for the children to be tutored.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "For us, going to school was-- again, it was a sign of resistance.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was-- it was a display of resistance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We did not live just by bread alone, literally.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That was I think the most graphic, the most real examples that were just not isolated examples but just were very common is-- is-- is going to-- having the tutors and-- and exchanging a crumb of bread for schooling.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, yeah, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As I was saying, that was a sign of resistance.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in some ways the children were very much involved, too, because when we went to-- to-- when we went to our hidden tutors, we had to hide our books.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Books were contraband, forbidden.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so we had-- we carried our books under our clothes.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
